    "https://doi.org/10.1038/s41592-023-02151-z handling ordinal data.",
    "Unlike other common multi-class metrics, such as (balanced) accuracy or MCC, it allows the user to specify different costs for different class confusions, thereby addressing the ordinal rating.",
    "However, our consortium deemed the (not widely known) metric EC generally more appropriate due to its favorable mathematical properties.",
    "Importantly, our framework does not intend to impose recommendations or act as a 'black box'; instead, it enables users to make educated decisions while considering ambiguities and trade-offs that may occur.",
